-- AT&T CEO Says He Applauds Augusta Decision to Admit First Women
-- B y   S c o t t   M o r i t z
-- 2012-08-20T16:18:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/at-t-ceo-says-he-applauds-augusta-decision-to-admit-first-women.html
AT&T Inc. (T)  Chief Executive Officer
Randall Stephenson, whose company sponsors the Masters
tournament at the Augusta National Golf Club, said he supports
the organization’s decision to admit its first female members.  “We applaud today’s historic announcement by Augusta
National and warmly welcome  Condoleezza Rice  and Darla Moore as
members of Augusta National,” he said in an e-mailed statement.  Rice, the former U.S. secretary of state, and Moore, a
partner at investment firm Rainwater Inc., were accepted as
members, the club said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Moritz in New York at 
 smoritz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
